to judicial review. The legislative body shall be a party in any[ such] appeal filed in the Circuit Court under
this subsection.
(4) The owner of the subject property and applicants who initiated the proceeding shall be made parties to the
appeal. Other persons speaking at the public hearing are not required to be made parties to such appeal.
(5) For purposes of this chapter, final action shall be deemed to have occurred on the calendar date when the vote
is taken to approve or disapprove the matter pending before the body.
Signed by Governor March 25, 2025.
